pokemonId1.name: Bulbasaur
pokemonId1.description: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

pokemonId2.name: Ivysaur
pokemonId2.description: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower's coming bloom.

pokemonId3.name: Venusaur
pokemonId3.genderDifference: The plant on the female Venusaur has got a seed coming out of the top.
pokemonId3.description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

pokemonId4.name: Charmander
pokemonId4.description: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

pokemonId5.name: Charmeleon
pokemonId5.description: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

pokemonId6.name: Charizard
pokemonId6.description: It is said that Charizard's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

pokemonId7.name: Squirtle
pokemonId7.description: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

pokemonId8.name: Wartortle
pokemonId8.description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

pokemonId9.name: Blastoise
pokemonId9.description: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

pokemonId10.name: Caterpie
pokemonId10.description: It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.

pokemonId11.name: Metapod
pokemonId11.description: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

pokemonId12.name: Butterfree
pokemonId12.genderDifference: There is an addition to the pattern on the Butterfree's wings when it is a female.
pokemonId12.description: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

pokemonId13.name: Weedle
pokemonId13.description: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.

pokemonId14.name: Kakuna
pokemonId14.description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

pokemonId15.name: Beedrill
pokemonId15.description: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.

pokemonId16.name: Pidgey
pokemonId16.description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

pokemonId17.name: Pidgeotto
pokemonId17.description: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.

pokemonId18.name: Pidgeot
pokemonId18.description: By flapping its wings with all its might, Pidgeot can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.

pokemonId19.name: Rattata
pokemonId19.genderDifference: There is an addition to the pattern on the Butterfree's wings when it is a female.
pokemonId19.description: It searches for food all day. It gnaws on hard objects to wear down its fangs, which grow constantly during its lifetime.

pokemonId20.name: Raticate
pokemonId20.genderDifference: The whiskers on the female Raticate are much smaller than the male Raticate.
pokemonId20.description: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.

pokemonId21.name: Spearow
pokemonId21.description: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

pokemonId22.name: Fearow
pokemonId22.description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

pokemonId23.name: Ekans
pokemonId23.description: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.

pokemonId24.name: Arbok
pokemonId24.description: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.

pokemonId25.name: Pikachu
pokemonId25.genderDifference: The whiskers on the female Raticate are much smaller than the male Raticate.
pokemonId25.description: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.

pokemonId26.name: Raichu
pokemonId26.genderDifference: The whiskers on the female Raticate are much smaller than the male Raticate.
pokemonId26.description: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

pokemonId27.name: Sandshrew
pokemonId27.description: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.

pokemonId28.name: Sandslash
pokemonId28.description: The spikes on its body are make up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.

pokemonId29.name: Nidoran♀
pokemonId29.description: While it does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the poison it secretes from barbs can be fatal.

pokemonId30.name: Nidorina
pokemonId30.description: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow slower than Nidorino's.

pokemonId31.name: Nidoqueen
pokemonId31.description: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.

pokemonId32.name: Nidoran♂
pokemonId32.description: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

pokemonId33.name: Nidorino
pokemonId33.description: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.

pokemonId34.name: Nidoking
pokemonId34.description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

pokemonId35.name: Clefairy
pokemonId35.description: On nights with a full moon, Clefairy gather from all over and dance. Bathing in moonlight makes them float.

pokemonId36.name: Clefable
pokemonId36.description: Their ears are sensitive enough to head a pin drop from over a mile away, so they're usually found in quiet places.

pokemonId37.name: Vulpix
pokemonId37.description: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

pokemonId38.name: Ninetales
pokemonId38.description: Each of its nine tails is imbued with a supernatural power, and it can live for a thousand years.

pokemonId39.name: Jigglypuff
pokemonId39.description: Looking into its cute, round eyes makes it start singing a song so pleasant listeners can't help but fall asleep.

pokemonId40.name: Wigglytuff
pokemonId40.description: Its fine fur feels so pleasant, those who accidentally touch it cannot take their hands away.

pokemonId41.name: Zubat
pokemonId41.genderDifference: Male Zubat have got larger teeth than the female Zubat
pokemonId41.description: It does not need eyes, because it emits ultrasonic waves to check its surroundings while it flies.

pokemonId42.name: Golbat
pokemonId42.genderDifference: Male Zubat have got larger teeth than the female Zubat
pokemonId42.description: Flitting around in the dead of night, it sinks its fangs into its prey and drains a nearly fatal amount of blood.

pokemonId43.name: Oddish
pokemonId43.description: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

pokemonId44.name: Gloom
pokemonId44.genderDifference: Male Zubat have got larger teeth than the female Zubat
pokemonId44.description: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

pokemonId45.name: Vileplume
pokemonId45.genderDifference: Male Zubat have got larger teeth than the female Zubat
pokemonId45.description: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

pokemonId46.name: Paras
pokemonId46.description: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host Paras.

pokemonId47.name: Parasect
pokemonId47.description: A mushroom grown larger than the host's body controls Parasect. It scatters poisonous spores.

pokemonId48.name: Venonat
pokemonId48.description: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

pokemonId49.name: Venomoth
pokemonId49.description: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.

pokemonId50.name: Diglett
pokemonId50.description: A Pokémon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.

pokemonId51.name: Dugtrio
pokemonId51.description: Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.

pokemonId52.name: Meowth
pokemonId52.description: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.

pokemonId53.name: Persian
pokemonId53.description: A very haughty Pokémon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

pokemonId54.name: Psyduck
pokemonId54.description: When headaches stimulate its brain cells, which are usually inactive, it can use a mysterious power.

pokemonId55.name: Golduck
pokemonId55.description: When its forehead shines mysteriously, Golduck can use the full extent of its power.

pokemonId56.name: Mankey
pokemonId56.description: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

pokemonId57.name: Primeape
pokemonId57.description: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

pokemonId58.name: Growlithe
pokemonId58.description: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.

pokemonId59.name: Arcanine
pokemonId59.description: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

pokemonId60.name: Poliwag
pokemonId60.description: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

pokemonId61.name: Poliwhirl
pokemonId61.description: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.

pokemonId62.name: Poliwrath
pokemonId62.description: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

pokemonId63.name: Abra
pokemonId63.description: Using its psychic power is such a strain on its brain that it needs to sleep for 18 hours a day.

pokemonId64.name: Kadabra
pokemonId64.genderDifference: Female Kadabra have smaller moustaches than their male counterparts
pokemonId64.description: It stares at its silver spoon to focus its mind. It emits more alpha waves while doing so.

pokemonId65.name: Alakazam
pokemonId65.genderDifference: Female Kadabra have smaller moustaches than their male counterparts
pokemonId65.description: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.

pokemonId66.name: Machop
pokemonId66.description: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.

pokemonId67.name: Machoke
pokemonId67.description: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.

pokemonId68.name: Machamp
pokemonId68.description: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.

pokemonId69.name: Bellsprout
pokemonId69.description: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.

pokemonId70.name: Weepinbell
pokemonId70.description: A Pokémon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

pokemonId71.name: Victreebel
pokemonId71.description: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honeylike scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

pokemonId72.name: Tentacool
pokemonId72.description: Because its body is almost entirely composed of water, it shrivels up if it is washed ashore.

pokemonId73.name: Tentacruel
pokemonId73.description: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.

pokemonId74.name: Geodude
pokemonId74.description: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.

pokemonId75.name: Graveler
pokemonId75.description: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokémon can stop it without difficulty.

pokemonId76.name: Golem
pokemonId76.description: Even dynamite can't harm its hard, boulderlike body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

pokemonId77.name: Ponyta
pokemonId77.description: As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.

pokemonId78.name: Rapidash
pokemonId78.description: When at an all-out gallop, its blazing mane sparkles, enhancing its beautiful appearance.

pokemonId79.name: Slowpoke
pokemonId79.description: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

pokemonId80.name: Slowbro
pokemonId80.description: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

pokemonId81.name: Magnemite
pokemonId81.description: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

pokemonId82.name: Magneton
pokemonId82.description: The stronger electromagnetic waves from the three linked Magnemite are enough to dry out surrounding moisture.

pokemonId83.name: Farfetch'd
pokemonId83.description: It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

pokemonId84.name: Doduo
pokemonId84.genderDifference: The different gendered Doduo have different colour necks. Male have black necks while female have pale brown necks.
pokemonId84.description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

pokemonId85.name: Dodrio
pokemonId85.genderDifference: The different gendered Doduo have different colour necks. Male have black necks while female have pale brown necks.
pokemonId85.description: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.

pokemonId86.name: Seel
pokemonId86.description: The colder it gets, the betterit feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.

pokemonId87.name: Dewgong
pokemonId87.description: Its streamlined body has low resistance, and it swims around cold oceans at a speed of eight knots.

pokemonId88.name: Grimer
pokemonId88.description: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

pokemonId89.name: Muk
pokemonId89.description: It's so stinky! Muk's body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.

pokemonId90.name: Shellder
pokemonId90.description: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.

pokemonId91.name: Cloyster
pokemonId91.description: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.

pokemonId92.name: Gastly
pokemonId92.description: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

pokemonId93.name: Haunter
pokemonId93.description: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

pokemonId94.name: Gengar
pokemonId94.description: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.

pokemonId95.name: Onix
pokemonId95.description: Opening its large mouth, it ingests massive amounts of soil and creates long tunnels.

pokemonId96.name: Drowzee
pokemonId96.description: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.

pokemonId97.name: Hypno
pokemonId97.genderDifference: The different gendered Hypno have varying sized collars. Female Hypno have larger collars while male Hypno have smaller ones
pokemonId97.description: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

pokemonId98.name: Krabby
pokemonId98.description: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.

pokemonId99.name: Kingler
pokemonId99.description: The larger pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

pokemonId100.name: Voltorb
pokemonId100.description: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.

pokemonId101.name: Electrode
pokemonId101.description: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

pokemonId102.name: Exeggcute
pokemonId102.description: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.

pokemonId103.name: Exeggutor
pokemonId103.description: It is called The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

pokemonId104.name: Cubone
pokemonId104.description: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.

pokemonId105.name: Marowak
pokemonId105.description: From its birth, this savage Pokémon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.

pokemonId106.name: Hitmonlee
pokemonId106.description: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

pokemonId107.name: Hitmonchan
pokemonId107.description: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.

pokemonId108.name: Lickitung
pokemonId108.description: Being licked by its long, saliva-covered tongue leaves a tingling sensation. Extending its tongue retracts its tail.

pokemonId109.name: Koffing
pokemonId109.description: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.

pokemonId110.name: Weezing
pokemonId110.description: Inhaling toxic fumes from trash and mixing them inside its body lets it spread an even fouler stench.

pokemonId111.name: Rhyhorn
pokemonId111.genderDifference: Different gendered Rhyhorn have varying sized horns. The male Rhyhorn have larger horns.
pokemonId111.description: Its powerful tackles can destroy anything. However, it is too slow witted to help people work.

pokemonId112.name: Rhydon
pokemonId112.genderDifference: Different gendered Rhyhorn have varying sized horns. The male Rhyhorn have larger horns.
pokemonId112.description: Standing on its hind legs freed its forelegs and made it smarter. It is very forgetful, however.

pokemonId113.name: Chansey
pokemonId113.description: A kindly Pokémon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

pokemonId114.name: Tangela
pokemonId114.description: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

pokemonId115.name: Kangaskhan
pokemonId115.description: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.

pokemonId116.name: Horsea
pokemonId116.description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

pokemonId117.name: Seadra
pokemonId117.description: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.

pokemonId118.name: Goldeen
pokemonId118.genderDifference: Different gendered Rhyhorn have varying sized horns. The male Rhyhorn have larger horns.
pokemonId118.description: Though it appears very elegant when swimming with fins unfurled, it can jab powerfully with its horn.

pokemonId119.name: Seaking
pokemonId119.genderDifference: Different gendered Rhyhorn have varying sized horns. The male Rhyhorn have larger horns.
pokemonId119.description: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

pokemonId120.name: Staryu
pokemonId120.description: As long as its red core remains, it can regenerate its body instantly, even if torn apart.

pokemonId121.name: Starmie
pokemonId121.description: Its core shines in many colors and sends radio signals into space to communicate with something.

pokemonId122.name: Mr. Mime
pokemonId122.description: It shapes an invisible wall in midair by minutely vibrating its fingertips to stop molecules in the air.

pokemonId123.name: Scyther
pokemonId123.genderDifference: The different gendered Scyther have varying sized abdomens. The female Scyther have the larger ones.
pokemonId123.description: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

pokemonId124.name: Jynx
pokemonId124.description: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.

pokemonId125.name: Electabuzz
pokemonId125.description: Research is progressing on storing lightning in Electabuzz so this energy can be used at any time.

pokemonId126.name: Magmar
pokemonId126.description: The scorching fire exhaled by Magmar forms heat waves around its body, making it hard to see the Pokémon clearly.

pokemonId127.name: Pinsir
pokemonId127.description: It grips prey with its powerful pincers and will not let go until the prey is torn in half.

pokemonId128.name: Tauros
pokemonId128.description: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.

pokemonId129.name: Magikarp
pokemonId129.genderDifference: The different gendered Scyther have varying sized abdomens. The female Scyther have the larger ones.
pokemonId129.description: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.

pokemonId130.name: Gyarados
pokemonId130.genderDifference: The gender difference in Gyarados is in regards to its whiskers. Male Gyarados have whiskers which match its body colours while female Gyarados' whiskers are white.
pokemonId130.description: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

pokemonId131.name: Lapras
pokemonId131.description: Able to understand human speech and very intelligent, it loves to swim in the sea with people on its back.

pokemonId132.name: Ditto
pokemonId132.description: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

pokemonId133.name: Eevee
pokemonId133.description: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

pokemonId134.name: Vaporeon
pokemonId134.description: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can't be seen when it melts away into water.

pokemonId135.name: Jolteon
pokemonId135.description: By storing electricity in its body, it can shoot its bristlelike fur like a barrage of missiles.

pokemonId136.name: Flareon
pokemonId136.description: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees F.

pokemonId137.name: Porygon
pokemonId137.description: A man-made Pokémon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely in cyberspace.

pokemonId138.name: Omanyte
pokemonId138.description: A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.

pokemonId139.name: Omastar
pokemonId139.description: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.

pokemonId140.name: Kabuto
pokemonId140.description: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.

pokemonId141.name: Kabutops
pokemonId141.description: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

pokemonId142.name: Aerodactyl
pokemonId142.description: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

pokemonId143.name: Snorlax
pokemonId143.description: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.

pokemonId144.name: Articuno
pokemonId144.description: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

pokemonId145.name: Zapdos
pokemonId145.description: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

pokemonId146.name: Moltres
pokemonId146.description: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

pokemonId147.name: Dratini
pokemonId147.description: It is called the Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

pokemonId148.name: Dragonair
pokemonId148.description: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

pokemonId149.name: Dragonite
pokemonId149.description: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

pokemonId150.name: Mewtwo
pokemonId150.description: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

pokemonId151.name: Mew
pokemonId151.description: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

pokemonId152.name: Chikorita
pokemonId152.description: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

pokemonId153.name: Bayleef
pokemonId153.description: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

pokemonId154.name: Meganium
pokemonId154.genderDifference: The antennae on the different gendered Meganium vary in size. Male Meganium have longer antennae
pokemonId154.description: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.

pokemonId155.name: Cyndaquil
pokemonId155.description: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

pokemonId156.name: Quilava
pokemonId156.description: It intimidates foes with the heat of its flames. The fire burns more strongly when it readies to fight.

pokemonId157.name: Typhlosion
pokemonId157.description: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.

pokemonId158.name: Totodile
pokemonId158.description: It has the habit of biting anything with its developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.

pokemonId159.name: Croconaw
pokemonId159.description: Once it bites down, it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

pokemonId160.name: Feraligatr
pokemonId160.description: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.

pokemonId161.name: Sentret
pokemonId161.description: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.

pokemonId162.name: Furret
pokemonId162.description: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.

pokemonId163.name: Hoothoot
pokemonId163.description: It marks time precisely. Some countries consider it to be a wise friend, versed in the world's ways.

pokemonId164.name: Noctowl
pokemonId164.description: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

pokemonId165.name: Ledyba
pokemonId165.genderDifference: The antennae on the different gendered Ledyba vary in size. Male Ledyba have longer antennae
pokemonId165.description: It is so timid, it can't move if it isn't with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.

pokemonId166.name: Ledian
pokemonId166.genderDifference: The antennae on the different gendered Ledyba vary in size. Male Ledyba have longer antennae
pokemonId166.description: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.

pokemonId167.name: Spinarak
pokemonId167.description: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong silk. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.

pokemonId168.name: Ariados
pokemonId168.description: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

pokemonId169.name: Crobat
pokemonId169.description: Having four wings allows it to fly more quickly and quietly so it can sneak up on prey without its noticing.

pokemonId170.name: Chinchou
pokemonId170.description: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.

pokemonId171.name: Lanturn
pokemonId171.description: Lanturn's light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed The Deep-Sea Star."

pokemonId172.name: Pichu
pokemonId172.description: The electric sacs in its cheeks are small. If even a little electricity leaks, it becomes shocked.

pokemonId173.name: Cleffa
pokemonId173.description: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

pokemonId174.name: Igglybuff
pokemonId174.description: Its body has a faintly sweet scent and is bouncy and soft. If it bounces even once, it cannot stop.

pokemonId175.name: Togepi
pokemonId175.description: It transforms the kindness and joy of others into happiness, which it stores in its shell.

pokemonId176.name: Togetic
pokemonId176.description: To share its happiness, it flies around the world seeking kind- hearted people.

pokemonId177.name: Natu
pokemonId177.description: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

pokemonId178.name: Xatu
pokemonId178.genderDifference: The gender difference on Xatu is only noticiable during its animation or from behind. Male Xatu have three stripes along their body while female Xatu have two.
pokemonId178.description: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.

pokemonId179.name: Mareep
pokemonId179.description: When cold weather increases static electricity, its wool doubles in size and the tip of its tail glows slightly.

pokemonId180.name: Flaaffy
pokemonId180.description: Not even downy wool will grow on its rubbery, nonconductive patches of skin that prevent electrical shock.

pokemonId181.name: Ampharos
pokemonId181.description: The tip of its tail shines so brightly it can be used to send sea-navigation beacons to distant foreign shores.

pokemonId182.name: Bellossom
pokemonId182.description: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

pokemonId183.name: Marill
pokemonId183.description: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it's fine even in rivers with strong currents.

pokemonId184.name: Azumarill
pokemonId184.description: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

pokemonId185.name: Sudowoodo
pokemonId185.genderDifference: The antennae on the different gendered Sudowoodo vary in size. Male Sudowoodo have longer antennae
pokemonId185.description: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.

pokemonId186.name: Politoed
pokemonId186.genderDifference: The antennae on the different gendered Sudowoodo vary in size. Male Sudowoodo have longer antennae
pokemonId186.description: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make Poliwag obey.

pokemonId187.name: Hoppip
pokemonId187.description: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

pokemonId188.name: Skiploom
pokemonId188.description: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

pokemonId189.name: Jumpluff
pokemonId189.description: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

pokemonId190.name: Aipom
pokemonId190.genderDifference: Aipom's gender difference is its head hair. The female Aipom have more hair on top of their head.
pokemonId190.description: It lives high among the treetops. It can use its tail as freely and cleverly as its hands.

pokemonId191.name: Sunkern
pokemonId191.description: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. Knowing it's weak, it simply feeds until it evolves.

pokemonId192.name: Sunflora
pokemonId192.description: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.

pokemonId193.name: Yanma
pokemonId193.description: By flapping its wings at high speed, it can fly freely through the air. Even sudden stops are no problem.

pokemonId194.name: Wooper
pokemonId194.genderDifference: Aipom's gender difference is its head hair. The female Aipom have more hair on top of their head.
pokemonId194.description: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

pokemonId195.name: Quagsire
pokemonId195.genderDifference: Aipom's gender difference is its head hair. The female Aipom have more hair on top of their head.
pokemonId195.description: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn't care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.

pokemonId196.name: Espeon
pokemonId196.description: Its fur is so sensitive, it can feel minute shifts in the air and predict the weatherand its foes' thoughts.

pokemonId197.name: Umbreon
pokemonId197.description: When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glaow faintly and it's filled with a mysterious power.

pokemonId198.name: Murkrow
pokemonId198.genderDifference: Aipom's gender difference is its head hair. The female Aipom have more hair on top of their head.
pokemonId198.description: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.

pokemonId199.name: Slowking
pokemonId199.description: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.

pokemonId200.name: Misdreavus
pokemonId200.description: A Pokémon that startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

pokemonId201.name: Unown
pokemonId201.description: When alone, nothing happens. However, if there are two or more, an odd power is said to emerge.

pokemonId202.name: Wobbuffet
pokemonId202.genderDifference: Wobbuffet's gender difference is rather unique. Female Wobbuffet are seen to be wearing lipstick.
pokemonId202.description: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. It is said to be proof the tail hides a secret.

pokemonId203.name: Girafarig
pokemonId203.genderDifference: Wobbuffet's gender difference is rather unique. Female Wobbuffet are seen to be wearing lipstick.
pokemonId203.description: The head on its tail contains a small brain. It can instinctively fight even while facing backward.

pokemonId204.name: Pineco
pokemonId204.description: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

pokemonId205.name: Forretress
pokemonId205.description: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.

pokemonId206.name: Dunsparce
pokemonId206.description: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

pokemonId207.name: Gligar
pokemonId207.genderDifference: Wobbuffet's gender difference is rather unique. Female Wobbuffet are seen to be wearing lipstick.
pokemonId207.description: It clamps on to its chosen prey then jabs the stinger on its tail into the prey while it's stunned with surprise.

pokemonId208.name: Steelix
pokemonId208.genderDifference: Wobbuffet's gender difference is rather unique. Female Wobbuffet are seen to be wearing lipstick.
pokemonId208.description: The iron it ingested with the soil it swallowed transformed its body and made it harder than diamonds.

pokemonId209.name: Snubbull
pokemonId209.description: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

pokemonId210.name: Granbull
pokemonId210.description: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

pokemonId211.name: Qwilfish
pokemonId211.description: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

pokemonId212.name: Scizor
pokemonId212.genderDifference: The different gendered Scizor have varying sized abdomens. The female Scizor have the larger ones.
pokemonId212.description: It raises its pincers with eyelike markings for intimidation. It also swings them down dangerously.

pokemonId213.name: Shuckle
pokemonId213.description: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

pokemonId214.name: Heracross
pokemonId214.genderDifference: The different gendered Scizor have varying sized abdomens. The female Scizor have the larger ones.
pokemonId214.description: No matter how heavy its opponents, it flings them far away with its prized horn.

pokemonId215.name: Sneasel
pokemonId215.genderDifference: The different gendered Scizor have varying sized abdomens. The female Scizor have the larger ones.
pokemonId215.description: A smart and sneaky Pokémon, it makes its opponents flinch by suddenly showing the claws hidden in its paws.

pokemonId216.name: Teddiursa
pokemonId216.description: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.

pokemonId217.name: Ursaring
pokemonId217.genderDifference: The different gendered Scizor have varying sized abdomens. The female Scizor have the larger ones.
pokemonId217.description: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.

pokemonId218.name: Slugma
pokemonId218.description: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

pokemonId219.name: Magcargo
pokemonId219.description: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.

pokemonId220.name: Swinub
pokemonId220.description: Rooting the tip of its snouth into the ground, it searches for food. Sometimes, it even digs up a hot spring.

pokemonId221.name: Piloswine
pokemonId221.genderDifference: The gender differences for Piloswine are based on its tusks. The male Piloswine have larger tusks than the female.
pokemonId221.description: With its excellent sense of smell, it's even able to find mushrooms that are buried under frozen ground.

pokemonId222.name: Corsola
pokemonId222.description: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.

pokemonId223.name: Remoraid
pokemonId223.description: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

pokemonId224.name: Octillery
pokemonId224.genderDifference: The gender differences for Piloswine are based on its tusks. The male Piloswine have larger tusks than the female.
pokemonId224.description: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

pokemonId225.name: Delibird
pokemonId225.description: It carries food all day long. When someone is lost in the mountains, it shares that food.

pokemonId226.name: Mantine
pokemonId226.description: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can fly over 300 feet out of the water from the surface of the ocean.

pokemonId227.name: Skarmory
pokemonId227.description: Its heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.

pokemonId228.name: Houndour
pokemonId228.description: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

pokemonId229.name: Houndoom
pokemonId229.genderDifference: The gender differences for Piloswine are based on its tusks. The male Piloswine have larger tusks than the female.
pokemonId229.description: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

pokemonId230.name: Kingdra
pokemonId230.description: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.

pokemonId231.name: Phanpy
pokemonId231.description: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

pokemonId232.name: Donphan
pokemonId232.genderDifference: The gender differences for Donphan are based on its tusks. The male Donphan have larger tusks than the female.
pokemonId232.description: It attacks by curling up, then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

pokemonId233.name: Porygon2
pokemonId233.description: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.

pokemonId234.name: Stantler
pokemonId234.description: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

pokemonId235.name: Smeargle
pokemonId235.description: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

pokemonId236.name: Tyrogue
pokemonId236.description: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.

pokemonId237.name: Hitmontop
pokemonId237.description: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by ten.

pokemonId238.name: Smoochum
pokemonId238.description: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.

pokemonId239.name: Elekid
pokemonId239.description: Spinning its arms around to generate electricity makes the area between its horns shine light blue.

pokemonId240.name: Magby
pokemonId240.description: It's small, but its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees F. Embers escape its mouth and nose when it breathes.

pokemonId241.name: Miltank
pokemonId241.description: It is said that kids who drink Miltank's milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

pokemonId242.name: Blissey
pokemonId242.description: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

pokemonId243.name: Raikou
pokemonId243.description: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.

pokemonId244.name: Entei
pokemonId244.description: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

pokemonId245.name: Suicune
pokemonId245.description: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

pokemonId246.name: Larvitar
pokemonId246.description: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

pokemonId247.name: Pupitar
pokemonId247.description: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

pokemonId248.name: Tyranitar
pokemonId248.description: The quakes caused when it walks make even great mountains crumble and change the surrounding terrain.

pokemonId249.name: Lugia
pokemonId249.description: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

pokemonId250.name: Ho-Oh
pokemonId250.description: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

pokemonId251.name: Celebi
pokemonId251.description: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

pokemonId252.name: Treecko
pokemonId252.description: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

pokemonId253.name: Grovyle
pokemonId253.description: It lives in dense jungles. While  closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

pokemonId254.name: Sceptile
pokemonId254.description: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

pokemonId255.name: Torchic
pokemonId255.description: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

pokemonId256.name: Combusken
pokemonId256.genderDifference: The male Combusken have larger feathers protuding from its head than the female.
pokemonId256.description: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.

pokemonId257.name: Blaziken
pokemonId257.genderDifference: The male Combusken have larger feathers protuding from its head than the female.
pokemonId257.description: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.

pokemonId258.name: Mudkip
pokemonId258.description: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

pokemonId259.name: Marshtomp
pokemonId259.description: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.

pokemonId260.name: Swampert
pokemonId260.description: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

pokemonId261.name: Poochyena
pokemonId261.description: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

pokemonId262.name: Mightyena
pokemonId262.description: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.

pokemonId263.name: Zigzagoon
pokemonId263.description: It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

pokemonId264.name: Linoone
pokemonId264.description: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

pokemonId265.name: Wurmple
pokemonId265.description: Often targeted by bird Pokémon, it desperately resists by releasing poison from its tail spikes.

pokemonId266.name: Silcoon
pokemonId266.description: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.

pokemonId267.name: Beautifly
pokemonId267.genderDifference: The red spot on Beautifly's wings is larger on the male than on the female
pokemonId267.description: Despite its looks, it is aggressive. It jabs with its long, thin mouth if disturbed while collecting pollen.

pokemonId268.name: Cascoon
pokemonId268.description: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

pokemonId269.name: Dustox
pokemonId269.genderDifference: The red spot on Beautifly's wings is larger on the male than on the female
pokemonId269.description: Toxic powder is scattered with each flap. At night, it is known to strip leaves off trees lining boulevards.

pokemonId270.name: Lotad
pokemonId270.description: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokémon that can't swim.

pokemonId271.name: Lombre
pokemonId271.description: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.

pokemonId272.name: Ludicolo
pokemonId272.genderDifference: The stripes on Ludicolo's body vary in size. The male Ludicolo's stripes are much thicker than the female's.
pokemonId272.description: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can't help breaking out into a dance.

pokemonId273.name: Seedot
pokemonId273.description: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

pokemonId274.name: Nuzleaf
pokemonId274.genderDifference: The stripes on Ludicolo's body vary in size. The male Ludicolo's stripes are much thicker than the female's.
pokemonId274.description: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.

pokemonId275.name: Shiftry
pokemonId275.genderDifference: The stripes on Ludicolo's body vary in size. The male Ludicolo's stripes are much thicker than the female's.
pokemonId275.description: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 ft/second that can level houses.

pokemonId276.name: Taillow
pokemonId276.description: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

pokemonId277.name: Swellow
pokemonId277.description: It circles the sky in search of prey. When it spots one, it dives steeply to catch the prey.

pokemonId278.name: Wingull
pokemonId278.description: It makes its nest on sheer cliffs. Riding the sea breeze, it glides up into the expansive skies.

pokemonId279.name: Pelipper
pokemonId279.description: Skimming the water's surface, it dips its large bill in the sea, scoops up food and water, and carries it.

pokemonId280.name: Ralts
pokemonId280.description: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

pokemonId281.name: Kirlia
pokemonId281.description: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

pokemonId282.name: Gardevoir
pokemonId282.description: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

pokemonId283.name: Surskit
pokemonId283.description: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

pokemonId284.name: Masquerain
pokemonId284.description: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.

pokemonId285.name: Shroomish
pokemonId285.description: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

pokemonId286.name: Breloom
pokemonId286.description: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

pokemonId287.name: Slakoth
pokemonId287.description: If it eats just three leaves a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20h ours a day.

pokemonId288.name: Vigoroth
pokemonId288.description: Its hearbeat is fast and its blood so agitated that it can't sit still for one secodn.

pokemonId289.name: Slaking
pokemonId289.description: This Pokémon lives lying on its side. It only rolls over and moves when there is no more grass to eat.

pokemonId290.name: Nincada
pokemonId290.description: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.

pokemonId291.name: Ninjask
pokemonId291.description: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

pokemonId292.name: Shedinja
pokemonId292.description: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one's spirit.

pokemonId293.name: Whismur
pokemonId293.description: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.

pokemonId294.name: Loudred
pokemonId294.description: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.

pokemonId295.name: Exploud
pokemonId295.description: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.

pokemonId296.name: Makuhita
pokemonId296.description: It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.

pokemonId297.name: Hariyama
pokemonId297.description: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

pokemonId298.name: Azurill
pokemonId298.description: It swings its large, nutrient-filled tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.

pokemonId299.name: Nosepass
pokemonId299.description: Its magnetic nose always faces north and draws iron objects to its body to protect itself better.

pokemonId300.name: Skitty
pokemonId300.description: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.

pokemonId301.name: Delcatty
pokemonId301.description: The reason it does not have a nest is that it simply searches for a clean, comfortable place then sleeps there.

pokemonId302.name: Sableye
pokemonId302.description: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.

pokemonId303.name: Mawile
pokemonId303.description: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

pokemonId304.name: Aron
pokemonId304.description: In order to build up its steel body, it eats iron ore. This pesky Pokémon is known to eat railroad tracks.

pokemonId305.name: Lairon
pokemonId305.description: Lairon fight over territory, and when their steel bodies collide, sparks fly.

pokemonId306.name: Aggron
pokemonId306.description: It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don't take it lightly.

pokemonId307.name: Meditite
pokemonId307.genderDifference: The placement of the ears varies on Meditite's different genders. Male Meditite's ears are high on the head while the female's ears are lower.
pokemonId307.description: It always trains deep in mountains. It levitates when it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.

pokemonId308.name: Medicham
pokemonId308.genderDifference: The placement of the ears varies on Meditite's different genders. Male Meditite's ears are high on the head while the female's ears are lower.
pokemonId308.description: It gains the ability to see the aura of its opponents by honing its mind through starvation.

pokemonId309.name: Electrike
pokemonId309.description: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.

pokemonId310.name: Manectric
pokemonId310.description: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

pokemonId311.name: Plusle
pokemonId311.description: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

pokemonId312.name: Minun
pokemonId312.description: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

pokemonId313.name: Volbeat
pokemonId313.description: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise's sweet aroma.

pokemonId314.name: Illumise
pokemonId314.description: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

pokemonId315.name: Roselia
pokemonId315.genderDifference: Roselia's body leaves are larger on the females than on the males
pokemonId315.description: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

pokemonId316.name: Gulpin
pokemonId316.genderDifference: Roselia's body leaves are larger on the females than on the males
pokemonId316.description: Almost all its body is its stomach. Its harsh digestive juices quickly dissolve anything it swallows.

pokemonId317.name: Swalot
pokemonId317.genderDifference: Roselia's body leaves are larger on the females than on the males
pokemonId317.description: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.

pokemonId318.name: Carvanha
pokemonId318.description: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.

pokemonId319.name: Sharpedo
pokemonId319.description: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as The Bully of the Sea."

pokemonId320.name: Wailmer
pokemonId320.description: It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out of its blowholes with great force.

pokemonId321.name: Wailord
pokemonId321.description: It can sometimes knock out oponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

pokemonId322.name: Numel
pokemonId322.genderDifference: The male Numel have larger humps than the females.
