pokemonId481.name: Mesprit
pokemonId481.description: When Mesprit flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.

pokemonId482.name: Azelf
pokemonId482.description: When Azelf flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.

pokemonId483.name: Dialga
pokemonId483.description: A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when Dialga's heart beats.

pokemonId484.name: Palkia
pokemonId484.description: A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with Palkia's every breath.

pokemonId485.name: Heatran
pokemonId485.description: Its body is made of rugged steel. However, it is partially melted in spots because of its own heat.

pokemonId486.name: Regigigas
pokemonId486.description: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

pokemonId487.name: Giratina
pokemonId487.description: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

pokemonId488.name: Cresselia
pokemonId488.description: On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.

pokemonId489.name: Phione
pokemonId489.description: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

pokemonId490.name: Manaphy
pokemonId490.description: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

pokemonId491.name: Darkrai
pokemonId491.description: To protect itself, it afflicts those around it with nightmares. However, it means no harm.

pokemonId492.name: Shaymin
pokemonId492.description: The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.

pokemonId493.name: Arceus
pokemonId493.description: It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing, then shaped the world.

pokemonId494.name: Victini
pokemonId494.description: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.

pokemonId495.name: Snivy
pokemonId495.description: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

pokemonId496.name: Servine
pokemonId496.description: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

pokemonId497.name: Serperior
pokemonId497.description: It only gives its all fighting against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior's noble eyes.

pokemonId498.name: Tepig
pokemonId498.description: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

pokemonId499.name: Pignite
pokemonId499.description: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.

pokemonId500.name: Emboar
pokemonId500.description: A flaring beard of fire is proof that it is fired up. It is adpet at using many different moves.

pokemonId501.name: Oshawott
pokemonId501.description: The scalchop on its stomach isn't just used for battle--it can be used to break open hard berries as well.

pokemonId502.name: Dewott
pokemonId502.description: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

pokemonId503.name: Samurott
pokemonId503.description: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.

pokemonId504.name: Patrat
pokemonId504.description: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

pokemonId505.name: Watchog
pokemonId505.description: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.

pokemonId506.name: Lillipup
pokemonId506.description: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.

pokemonId507.name: Herdier
pokemonId507.description: This very loyal Pokémo helps trainers, and it also takes care of other Pokémon.

pokemonId508.name: Stoutland
pokemonId508.description: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.

pokemonId509.name: Purrloin
pokemonId509.description: Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.

pokemonId510.name: Liepard
pokemonId510.description: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.

pokemonId511.name: Pansage
pokemonId511.description: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

pokemonId512.name: Simisage
pokemonId512.description: It strikes its enemies with a thorn-covered tail. The leaf on its head is bitter.

pokemonId513.name: Pansear
pokemonId513.description: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.

pokemonId514.name: Simisear
pokemonId514.description: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

pokemonId515.name: Panpour
pokemonId515.description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.

pokemonId516.name: Simipour
pokemonId516.description: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

pokemonId517.name: Munna
pokemonId517.description: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.

pokemonId518.name: Musharna
pokemonId518.description: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

pokemonId519.name: Pidove
pokemonId519.description: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.

pokemonId520.name: Tranquill
pokemonId520.description: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets seperated from its Trainer.

pokemonId521.name: Unfezant
pokemonId521.genderDifference: Unfezant has a major gender difference. The male version has a green belly and wears a mask similar the masks worn in renaissance Italy while the female Unfezant have no mask and have a brown body.
pokemonId521.description: Males swing the plumage on their heads to threaten others, but females are better at flying.

pokemonId522.name: Blitzle
pokemonId522.description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricty. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

pokemonId523.name: Zebstrika
pokemonId523.description: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

pokemonId524.name: Roggenrola
pokemonId524.description: The hexagonal-shaped hole is its ear. It has a tendency to walk in the direction the sound is coming from.

pokemonId525.name: Boldore
pokemonId525.description: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swifly moves front to back and left to right.

pokemonId526.name: Gigalith
pokemonId526.description: The solar rays it absorbs are processed in its energy core and fired as a ball of light.

pokemonId527.name: Woobat
pokemonId527.description: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

pokemonId528.name: Swoobat
pokemonId528.description: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.

pokemonId529.name: Drilbur
pokemonId529.description: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30mph.

pokemonId530.name: Excadrill
pokemonId530.description: Forming a drill with its steel claws and head, it can bore through a steel plate, no matter how thick it is.

pokemonId531.name: Audino
pokemonId531.description: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.

pokemonId532.name: Timburr
pokemonId532.description: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

pokemonId533.name: Gurdurr
pokemonId533.description: With strengthened bodies, they skillfully wield steel beams to take down buildings.

pokemonId534.name: Conkeldurr
pokemonId534.description: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

pokemonId535.name: Tympole
pokemonId535.description: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans and warns others of danger.

pokemonId536.name: Palpitoad
pokemonId536.description: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, stick tongue to immobilize its opponents.

pokemonId537.name: Seismitoad
pokemonId537.description: By putting power into its bumps, it creates vibrations and increase the power of its punches.

pokemonId538.name: Throh
pokemonId538.description: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

pokemonId539.name: Sawk
pokemonId539.description: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.

pokemonId540.name: Sewaddle
pokemonId540.description: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothers out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

pokemonId541.name: Swadloon
pokemonId541.description: Preferring dark, damp places, it spends the entire day eating fallen leaves that lie around it.

pokemonId542.name: Leavanny
pokemonId542.description: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.

pokemonId543.name: Venipede
pokemonId543.description: Using the feelers on its head and tail, it picks up vibrations in the air to determine its prey's location and state.

pokemonId544.name: Whirlipede
pokemonId544.description: Storing energy for evolution, it sits. But, when predators approach, it moves to stab them with poison spikes.

pokemonId545.name: Scolipede
pokemonId545.description: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.

pokemonId546.name: Cottonee
pokemonId546.description: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

pokemonId547.name: Whimsicott
pokemonId547.description: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes.

pokemonId548.name: Petilil
pokemonId548.description: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.

pokemonId549.name: Lilligant
pokemonId549.description: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.

pokemonId550.name: Basculin
pokemonId550.description: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.

pokemonId551.name: Sandile
pokemonId551.description: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their  body temperature from dropping.

pokemonId552.name: Krokorok
pokemonId552.description: Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals.

pokemonId553.name: Krookodile
pokemonId553.description: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.

pokemonId554.name: Darumaka
pokemonId554.description: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 F.

pokemonId555.name: Darmanitan
pokemonId555.description: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.

pokemonId556.name: Maractus
pokemonId556.description: When it moves rhythmically, it makes a sound similar to maracas, making the surprised Pokémon flee.

pokemonId557.name: Dwebble
pokemonId557.description: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

pokemonId558.name: Crustle
pokemonId558.description: When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.

pokemonId559.name: Scraggy
pokemonId559.description: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.

pokemonId560.name: Scrafty
pokemonId560.description: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.

pokemonId561.name: Sigilyph
pokemonId561.description: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

pokemonId562.name: Yamask
pokemonId562.description: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves. Each retains memories of its former life.

pokemonId563.name: Cofagrigus
pokemonId563.description: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

pokemonId564.name: Tirtouga
pokemonId564.description: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. It swam skillfully and dove to depths beyond half a mile.

pokemonId565.name: Carracosta
pokemonId565.description: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.

pokemonId566.name: Archen
pokemonId566.description: It was revived from an ancient fossil. Not able to fly, it lived in treetops and hopped from one branch to another.

pokemonId567.name: Archeops
pokemonId567.description: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25mph.

pokemonId568.name: Trubbish
pokemonId568.description: Wanting more garbage, they follow people who litter. They always belch poison gas.

pokemonId569.name: Garbodor
pokemonId569.description: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

pokemonId570.name: Zorua
pokemonId570.description: It changes so it looks just like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.

pokemonId571.name: Zoroark
pokemonId571.description: Stories say those tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.

pokemonId572.name: Minccino
pokemonId572.description: Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.

pokemonId573.name: Cinccino
pokemonId573.description: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

pokemonId574.name: Gothita
pokemonId574.description: It stares intently at everything. It can become so obsessed with watching that it doesn't notice attacks.

pokemonId575.name: Gothorita
pokemonId575.description: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

pokemonId576.name: Gothitelle
pokemonId576.description: It can see the future from the movement of the stars. When it learns its Trainer's life span, it cries in sadness.

pokemonId577.name: Solosis
pokemonId577.description: Because their obdies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.

pokemonId578.name: Duosion
pokemonId578.description: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

pokemonId579.name: Reuniclus
pokemonId579.description: They use psychic power to control their arms, which are made of a special liquid. They can crush boulders physically.

pokemonId580.name: Ducklett
pokemonId580.description: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

pokemonId581.name: Swanna
pokemonId581.description: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

pokemonId582.name: Vanillite
pokemonId582.description: Theoretically, this Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. Their breath is -58 F.

pokemonId583.name: Vanillish
pokemonId583.description: They cool down the surrounding air and create ice particles, which they use to freeze their foes.

pokemonId584.name: Vanilluxe
pokemonId584.description: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.

pokemonId585.name: Deerling
pokemonId585.description: Their colouring changes according to the seasons and can be slightly affected by the temperature and humidity as well.

pokemonId586.name: Sawsbuck
pokemonId586.description: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

pokemonId587.name: Emolga
pokemonId587.description: It glides on its outstretched membrane while shocking foes with the electricty stored in the pounches on its cheeks.

pokemonId588.name: Karrablast
pokemonId588.description: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

pokemonId589.name: Escavalier
pokemonId589.description: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

pokemonId590.name: Foongus
pokemonId590.description: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball then releases poison spores.

pokemonId591.name: Amoonguss
pokemonId591.description: It moves the caps on both arms and does a dance to lure prey. It prefers damp places.

pokemonId592.name: Frillish
pokemonId592.genderDifference: Frillish's gender different is primarily body colour. The male ones have a blue coloured body and have a frowning face while the female ones are pink with frilly tendrils and have a happier disposition
pokemonId592.description: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

pokemonId593.name: Jellicent
pokemonId593.genderDifference: Frillish's gender different is primarily body colour. The male ones have a blue coloured body and have a frowning face while the female ones are pink with frilly tendrils and have a happier disposition
pokemonId593.description: Its body is mostly seawater. It's said there's a castle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.

pokemonId594.name: Alomomola
pokemonId594.description: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

pokemonId595.name: Joltik
pokemonId595.description: Since it can't generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.

pokemonId596.name: Galvantula
pokemonId596.description: It creates barriers from electrified silk that stuns foes. This works as a weapon as well as a defense.

pokemonId597.name: Ferroseed
pokemonId597.description: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

pokemonId598.name: Ferrothorn
pokemonId598.description: By swinging around its three spiky feelers and shooting spikes, it can obliterate an opponent.

pokemonId599.name: Klink
pokemonId599.description: Two bodies comprise a fixed pair. They spin around each other to generate electricity.

pokemonId600.name: Klang
pokemonId600.description: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it luanches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.

pokemonId601.name: Klinklang
pokemonId601.description: The minigear spins at high speed. Then energy from the red core charges the minigear to make it ready to fire.

pokemonId602.name: Tynamo
pokemonId602.description: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathes to unleash a powerful electric shock.

pokemonId603.name: Eelektrik
pokemonId603.description: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.

pokemonId604.name: Eelektross
pokemonId604.description: It latches onto prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.

pokemonId605.name: Elgyem
pokemonId605.description: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.

pokemonId606.name: Beheeyem
pokemonId606.description: Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three fingers, but those patterns haven't been decoded.

pokemonId607.name: Litwick
pokemonId607.description: Its flame is usually out, but it starts shining when it absorbs life force from people or Pokémon.

pokemonId608.name: Lampent
pokemonId608.description: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.

pokemonId609.name: Chandelure
pokemonId609.description: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

pokemonId610.name: Axew
pokemonId610.description: Its large tusks have a tendency to break, but each time they grow back, they grow in harder and sturdier.

pokemonId611.name: Fraxure
pokemonId611.description: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

pokemonId612.name: Haxorus
pokemonId612.description: Its tusks are incredibly destructive. They can easily slice through a thick, sturdy steel column every time.

pokemonId613.name: Cubchoo
pokemonId613.description: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

pokemonId614.name: Beartic
pokemonId614.description: They love the cold seas of the north. They create pathways around the ocean waters by freezing their own breath.

pokemonId615.name: Cryogonal
pokemonId615.description: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 F.

pokemonId616.name: Shelmet
pokemonId616.description: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.

pokemonId617.name: Accelgor
pokemonId617.description: When its body dries out, it weakens. So it wraps a membrane around itself for protection while it spits poison.

pokemonId618.name: Stunfisk
pokemonId618.description: When its opponent can't be paralyzed, it contorts itself with unexpected speed and flops away.

pokemonId619.name: Mienfoo
pokemonId619.description: It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.

pokemonId620.name: Mienshao
pokemonId620.description: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

pokemonId621.name: Druddigon
pokemonId621.description: It runs through the narrow tunnels formed by Excadrill and Onix. It uses its sharp claws to catch prey.

pokemonId622.name: Golett
pokemonId622.description: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.

pokemonId623.name: Golurk
pokemonId623.description: Golurk were created to protect people and Pokémon. They run on a mysterious energy.

pokemonId624.name: Pawniard
pokemonId624.description: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.

pokemonId625.name: Bisharp
pokemonId625.description: This pitiless Pokémon commands a group of Pawniard to hound prey into immobility. It then moves in to finish the prey off.

pokemonId626.name: Bouffalant
pokemonId626.description: They are known to charge so wildly that if a trainer were toenter their territory, they would send it flying.

pokemonId627.name: Rufflet
pokemonId627.description: It stands up to massive opponents, not out of courage, but out of recklessness. But that is how it gets stronger.

pokemonId628.name: Braviary
pokemonId628.description: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.

pokemonId629.name: Vullaby
pokemonId629.description: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

pokemonId630.name: Mandibuzz
pokemonId630.description: They fly in circles around the sky. When they spot prey, they attack and carry it back to their nest with ease.

pokemonId631.name: Heatmor
pokemonId631.description: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

pokemonId632.name: Durant
pokemonId632.description: Individuals each play different roles in driving Heatmor, their natural predator, away from their colony.

pokemonId633.name: Deino
pokemonId633.description: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

pokemonId634.name: Zweilous
pokemonId634.description: The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be their leader.

pokemonId635.name: Hydreigon
pokemonId635.description: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!.

pokemonId636.name: Larvesta
pokemonId636.description: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.

pokemonId637.name: Volcarona
pokemonId637.description: Thought to be an emobiment of the sun, it appeared during a bitterly cold winter and saved Pokémon from freezing..

pokemonId638.name: Cobalion
pokemonId638.description: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

pokemonId639.name: Terrakion
pokemonId639.description: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

pokemonId640.name: Virizion
pokemonId640.description: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

pokemonId641.name: Tornadus
pokemonId641.description: In every direction it flies, creating winds so powerful, they blow everything away.

pokemonId642.name: Thundurus
pokemonId642.description: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

pokemonId643.name: Reshiram
pokemonId643.description: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

pokemonId644.name: Zekrom
pokemonId644.description: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.
